SIMPLE: eye_opener
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: eye opener
<hw>eye opener</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>That which makes the
eyes open, as startling news or occurrence; something which causes one
to suddenly understand what was not previously known.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A drink of liquor, especially the first one in the
morning.</def> <mark>[U. S. Slang]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>eye-opening</ent>⟦br⟧
